<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine Service, Model Year 1994 - 1998 - CYLINDER HEAD AND VALVES -
        Cylinder Head Disassembly
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Cylinder Head Disassembly</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>Before removing the cylinder head, remove the following items. Refer to the appropriate section for
                the correct removal procedure:
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Fuel lines and filter assembly</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>High pressure hydraulic lines</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Engine harness connections</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="1">
            <title>Remove Left Valve Cover</title>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent damage to the turbocharger, cover the turbocharger inlet port.</para>
                </caution>
                <note>
                    <para>If equipped, the crankcase breather elbow and the road draft tube must be removed before the
                        left valve cover can be removed.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the wiring harness from the valve cover gasket.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the glow plug relay. See
                    <emph type="bold">Section 10, Engine Electrical</emph>, for the procedure.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1200405" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg3/EG3310.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="328px"
                         scalefitheight="392px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Removing the Left Valve Cover</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Valve Cover Mounting Bolt</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Valve Cover Mounting Stud Nut</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Valve Cover</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove valve cover mounting hardware. Remove the valve cover from the cylinder head.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The breather does not need to be removed at this point.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
